---

<section class="pricing" id="pricing" aria-labelledby="pricing-title">
  <div class="pricing-inner">
    <div class="pricing-header reveal">
      <div class="section-num">05</div>
      <h2 class="section-title" id="pricing-title">How pricing works.</h2>
      <p class="pricing-lede">
        Every job is quoted individually — rooms vary too much for a flat rate.
        But here's roughly how we think about it.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="pricing-grid">
      <div class="pricing-card reveal">
        <div class="card-num" aria-hidden="true">i.</div>
        <h3>Labor</h3>
        <p>
          Typically the largest line item. We price by complexity, not by the
          hour: ceilings, stairwells, bookcase backs, and grasscloth with
          visible seams cost more than a straightforward four-wall powder room.
          You'll know the labor cost before we start.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="pricing-card reveal">
        <div class="card-num" aria-hidden="true">ii.</div>
        <h3>Materials</h3>
        <p>
          The paper is your budget, not ours. Rolls run anywhere from $80 to
          $400 and up, and most rooms need four to ten rolls depending on
          pattern repeat and wall area. We'll calculate exact yardage before
          you order — no guessing, no overage surprises.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="pricing-card reveal">
        <div class="card-num" aria-hidden="true">iii.</div>
        <h3>Sourcing</h3>
        <p>
          If you'd like help finding the right paper, sourcing and styling is
          available as part of your project. We'll research options, build a
          shortlist, and help you make the final call — so you're not spending
          hours down a wallpaper rabbit hole alone.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="pricing-footer reveal">
      <!-- TODO(margaret): uncomment and fill in pricing range if desired -->
      <!-- <p class="pricing-range">Most powder rooms land between ${{ PRICING_RANGE }} all-in (labor + prep — materials are separate). Larger or more complex rooms are quoted individually.</p> -->
      <a href="#contact" class="btn-primary">
        Get a quote for your room
        <span class="arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .pricing {
    padding: 120px 40px;
    background: var(--bg);
  }

  .pricing-inner {
    max-width: 1400px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .pricing-header {
    margin-bottom: 80px;
  }

  .pricing-header .section-title {
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }

  .pricing-lede {
    font-size: 20px;
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    max-width: 560px;
  }

  .pricing-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 2px;
    background: var(--rule);
    border: 1px solid var(--rule);
    margin-bottom: 64px;
  }

  .pricing-card {
    background: var(--paper);
    padding: 48px 40px 56px;
    position: relative;
  }

  .card-num {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
    font-size: 14px;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--ink-mute);
    position: absolute;
    top: 30px;
    right: 30px;
  }

  .pricing-card h3 {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 34px;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    margin-bottom: 18px;
    color: var(--ink);
  }

  .pricing-card p {
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
  }

  .pricing-footer {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 28px;
  }

  .pricing-range {
    font-size: 17px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    max-width: 560px;
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .pricing { padding: 80px 20px; }
    .pricing-header { margin-bottom: 56px; }
    .pricing-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>
